Guidelines I used for the creation of the icons (everything based on Gimp):

- rely on PNG files (high resolution 512x512) exported from icns files using
  http://iconverticons.com/
- Most of the icon comes from Mac OS X bundle (see
  /System/Library/CoreServices/CoreTypes.bundle/Contents/Resources/)
- To get the drive icon in Apple format: 
  * 'Get info' on the drive, copy the top left icon
  * open Preview, Edit -> 'Copy from Clipboard'
  * Save as

Convention I used:

- Text police (Gimp): Trebuchet MS Bold, size 80 (except 'sparsebundle': size 55)
- Text window size: 194*100
- Size of the sub-elements (In general: 310x310 px)
       Drive/SSH bottom right: 300x300
       File folder bottom right: 275x275
       OK, KO: 310x310 top left
  Lock: depends, 275x275 over full size icon 


